arn.description:
Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the framework.
* `control_sets[*].id` - Unique identifier for the framework control set.

complianceType.description: Compliance type that the new custom framework supports, such as `CIS` or `HIPAA`.

controlSets.description:
Control sets that are associated with the framework. See `control_sets` below.

The following arguments are optional:

frameworkType.description: Framework type, such as a custom framework or a standard framework.

tags.description: A map of tags to assign to the framework. If configured with a provider `default_tags` configuration block present, tags with matching keys will overwrite those defined at the provider-level.

complianceType.description: Compliance type that the new custom framework supports, such as `CIS` or `HIPAA`.

controlSets.description:
Control sets that are associated with the framework. See `control_sets` below.

The following arguments are optional:

tags.description: A map of tags to assign to the framework. If configured with a provider `default_tags` configuration block present, tags with matching keys will overwrite those defined at the provider-level.

stateInputs.description: Input properties used for looking up and filtering Framework resources.
